				COVID-19 Plan for JSRHS




													Details							









					Last Updated: 29 March 2020				







  Print  

  Email 

 PDF 





Dear John Stark Community,

As you are aware, SAU24 and John Stark Regional High School are closed due to COVID-19. The closure will run at least through April 3, 2020.  Despite this closure, we are committed to continuing to provide quality learning opportunities to our students.  To do so, we will be implementing online learning beginning on Wednesday, March 18, 2020.  


Until further notice, the building is closed to all staff and students. Only essential staff will be allowed in the building.  If you need to reach a staff member, you will need to do so by email. CLICK HERE to access the staff email directory.   

Our online remote learning will be facilitated through Google Classroom.  Teachers will attempt to be available from 9:00am until 1:00pm each day, but may post alternate times within their Google Classroom.  Teachers will generally respond to emails within 24 hours; however, please understand that personal situations may impact their ability to do so.  



CLICK HERE to go the the Digital Learning Technology Support for Families Page.

 

Weekly Plan

Mondays: Advisory-based Digital Learning Mondays (see reference below); Students will receive an email from their Advisor and should respond.  The resources for Digital Learning Mondays may be found at this link.

Tuesday & Thursday: A Days Course-Specific Activity; Students will receive an email from their Advisor and should respond

Wednesday & Friday: B Days Course-Specific Activity; Students will receive an email from their Advisor and should respond

This plan will be in place until at least April 3rd.  If the closure continues, we will also continue with this same plan.

All teachers are committed to thoughtfully planning learning activities for our students.  These activities will be related to course competencies with the goal of moving learning forward.

Communication 

Clarity and consistency of communication is essential for the comfort and success of all.  All stakeholders should adhere to the following guidelines for the duration of this adventure:


Advisors will check in, via email, with the students in their advisory every day. Students should reply to the daily email.

Classroom teachers may post work the morning of a specific class or may post the work for the entire week beginning on Monday.  

Students are expected to complete all assignments and contact their teacher if additional support is needed.


Digital Learning Mondays



Students will be using the JSR Digital Learning Mondays website to guide their learning on Mondays during the extended school closure. Directions are provided on the website.



Grades


Accountability for all specific courses will be handled by individual classroom teachers and those related assignments and activities.

PowerSchool will be up-to-date for grades.


School Counseling 

While School Counseling is best done in person, we have systems in place to support students remotely. 



You can access our current resources by navigating the School Counseling website. A few have been highlighted below. 




You can send a question to your counselor or Dr. Zielinski or Mrs. Getman via email and expect a response within 24 hours. 



Counselors will respond to concerns regarding post-secondary plans. 



Scholarship questions can be sent to Mrs. Glynn, who will respond within 48 hours. Please plan accordingly. 




If you still need to schedule your Junior Meeting, please email your counselor.



